  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  upper-limb motor impairments due to stroke

          -  metacarpophalangeal and proximal interphalangeal joints of fingers can be extended to
             180 degree passively

          -  spasticity during extension at the finger joints is lower than 3 as measured by the
             Modified Ashworth Scale

          -  detectable voluntary EMG signals from the flexor digitorum and extensor digitorum
             muscles of the paretic hand

          -  have sufficient cognition to follow the experimental instructions

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  have other neurological, neuromuscular, and orthopedic diseases

          -  have shoulder or arm contracture/pain
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
